>> http://puhep1.princeton.edu/~mcdonald/examples/power.pdf
>> a rod of radius r =3D 1 cm, l =3D 1 m, with 1200 turns would have a Q of=
 30 at 1 MHz, a radiation resistance of 100 Ohms, and would capture the max=
imum possible power (rather than 1e-8 of maximum as in typical AM radios).
>> =

>> If the effective loss resistance at 1 MHz of this high-tech ferrite is l=
ess than 100 Ohms, this could be a good antenna for a crystal radio set.  I=
 don=92t have information on this =96 which might prove to be the sticking =
point.
